Package: functional-shell
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 4.0)
Suggests: bash-completion
Description: Functional programming utilities for shell scripting
 Functional Shell provides map and filter commands that bring functional
 programming concepts to shell scripting. These utilities allow you to
 transform and filter data streams using a wide range of operations.
 .
 Key features:
  - map command for transforming data (string, arithmetic, file operations)
  - filter command for selecting data based on conditions
  - Extensive operation library (40+ operations)
  - Chainable operations for complex data processing
  - Shell completion support for bash and zsh
 .
 Common use cases include processing file lists, log analysis, data
 transformation, and general shell pipeline enhancement.